en kultur- und geistesgeschichtlichen Hintergrundinformationen zur Entstehung des christlichen Mönchtums werden in einem längeren Vorspann ausgebreitet. Der synoptische Vergleich wird hier zum ersten Mal gezogen.  aThis volume contains the synoptic presentation of the vita of Pachomius, founder of Coptic monasteries, who lived from the late third until the mid-forth century CE. The main focus is placed on the Sahidic text, which is flanked by the Bohairic and Greek versions for comparison. The long preface gives a detailed overview of the history and formation of Christian monasticism.  aIssued also in print.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn German.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 06. Mrz 2024) 4aHagiographie. 4aKoptisch. 4aKoptische Kirche. 4aVita Pachomii. 7aHISTORY / Ancient / Egypt.2bisacsh  aCoptic Monasticism.  aHagiography.  aPachomius.1 aBojowald, Stefan, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDG Plus DeG Package 2023 Part 1z978311117578208iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2023z9783111318912oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Theol., Relig.Stud., Jewish Stud. 2023z9783111318820oZDB-23-DGF0 cprintz978311071618440uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978311071635140uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9783110716351423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9783110716351/original  a978-3-11-117578-2  DG Plus DeG Package 2023 Part 1b2023  aEBA_CL_CL  aEBA_CL_PLTLJSIS  aEBA_DGALL  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_SSHALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aZDB-23-DGFb2023  aZDB-23-DGGb2023